author: Rebecca Thurlow
title: China Steps Up Investments in Australian Ports
text:
China’s Landbridge Group bought a long-term lease in the Port of Darwin in Australia’s north for 506 million Australian dollars (US$370 million), as the country seeks to capitalize on rising Chinese demand for imported food and overseas travel.
The deal comes after China Merchants Group teamed up with Australian fund-manager Hastings Funds Management in April last year to buy the lease on the Port of Newcastle in New South Wales...
